<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,1982,2045]" lastBlockId="15.[151,1437,153,467]" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="166" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">
This genus, previously containing a single species in 
<collectingCountry box="[746,835,1982,2008]" name="Sweden" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">Sweden</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[889,975,1982,2008]" name="Finland" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">Finland</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Gagne, R. J. &amp; Jaschhof, M." box="[989,1264,1982,2008]" pageId="14" pageNumber="165" refId="ref19883" refString="Gagne, R. J. &amp;. Jaschhof, M. (2017) A Catalog of the Cecidomyiidae (Diptera) of the World. 4 th Edition. Digital Version 3. Available from: http: // www. ars. usda. gov / ARSUserFiles / 80420580 / Gagne _ 2017 _ World _ Cat _ 4 th _ ed. pdf (accessed 15 August 2019)" type="url" year="2017">Gagn√© &amp; Jaschhof 2017</bibRefCitation>
), is shown here to have a second member, which we recently discovered in 
<collectingCountry box="[807,899,2018,2044]" name="Sweden" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">Sweden</collectingCountry>
. Several characters of the new species require us to update the generic definition (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Jaschhof, M. &amp; Jaschhof, C." box="[559,914,153,179]" pageId="15" pageNumber="166" pagination="1 - 392" refId="ref20090" refString="Jaschhof, M. &amp; Jaschhof, C. (2013) The Porricondylinae (Diptera: Cecidomyiidae) of Sweden, with notes on extralimital species. Studia dipterologica Supplement, 20, 1 - 392." type="journal article" year="2013">Jaschhof &amp; Jaschhof 2013: 292</bibRefCitation>
), as follows. Based on the presence of 
<specimenCount box="[1348,1436,153,179]" pageId="15" pageNumber="166" type="male">11 male</specimenCount>
flagellomeres and the absence of basitarsal spines, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jaschhof" authorityYear="2013" box="[717,834,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Paurodyla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[717,834,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">Paurodyla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to generic group Ab. The flagellomeral necks of males (females are unknown) have microtrichia, a highly unusual trait among 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gagne &amp; Jaschhof" baseAuthorityYear="2017" box="[1062,1228,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Porricondylini">Porricondylini</taxonomicName>
. The gonostylus is concave inside (medially) and slightly bilobed apically, with the ventral lobe being larger and strongly bent; both lobes are armed with teeth of varying outline. The gonocoxal synsclerite, which is as long as broad or even longer, has no or only small processes, a large, non-setose area ventrobasally, and a sharply contoured, broadly rounded ventrobasal edge. The strongly sclerotized parameres, which are largely separate from each other (there is only a narrow transverse bridge anteriorly), are of varying structure. The apex of the aedeagal apodeme is conspicuously narrowed.
</paragraph>
